<P>What is there that a man may not turn unto his good&punc; <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> which offendeth us mo&s;t, there is more ground for <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="2 words"> hatred. Man would be reconciled to him of whom he <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">. What murdereth he, but what he hateth?</P>
<P>If thou art prevented of a benefit, fly not into a rage; the lo&s;s of thy rea&s;on, is the want of a greater.</P>
