<P>The root of ambition is in every man; but it ri&s;eth not in all: &s;car keepeth it down in &s;ome; in many it is &s;uppre&s;&s;ed by mode&s;ty.</P>
<P>It is the inner garment of the &s;oul; the fir&s;t thing put on by it with the fle&s;h&punc; and the la&s;t it layeth down at its &s;eparation from it.</P>
