<P N="250">250. True eloquence con&s;i&s;ts in &s;aying all that ought to be &s;aid&punc; and in &s;aying no more.</P>
<P N="251">251. There are &s;ome per&s;ons who&s;e defects become them; and others, who have the misfortune to di&s;plea&s;e with their good qua|lities.</P>
