<P N="259">259. The plea&s;ure of love is loving: and a man is more happy in the pa&s;&s;ion he feels, than in that which he gives.</P>
<P N="260">260. Civility, is a de&s;ire of receiving civility, and of being e&s;teem|ed well bred.</P>
<P N="261">261. The education we commonly give young people, is a &s;econd &s;elf-love, with which we in&s;pire them.</P>
