<P N="466">466. Of all the violent pa&s;&s;ions, that which is the lea&s;t unbecom|ing of women, is love.</P>
<P N="467">467. Vanity makes us do more things again&s;t our inclination than rea&s;on.</P>
<P N="468">468. There are &s;ome great talents that are formed by bad qualities.</P>
<P N="469">469. We never pa&s;&s;ionately de&s;ire the thing, which we only de&s;ire from the dictates of rea&s;on.</P>
