<P N="481">481. Nothing is more rare than true good-nature; tho&s;e even who fancy they have it, have, commonly, nothing but either ea&s;ine&s;s, or complai&s;ance.</P>
<P N="482">482. The mind, betwixt lazine&s;s and con&s;tancy, is fixed to what is either ea&s;y or agreeable to it; this habit always &s;ets the bounds to
